B6%BB%E0%B7%83%E0%B6%B3%E0%B7%94%E0%B6%B1/%E0%B7%83%E0%B7%94%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%BD%E0%B7%8A-%E0%B7%83%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%8A-%E0%B6%B8%E0%B6%A7-%E0%B6%B8%E0%B7%8F%E0%B7%80-%E0%B6%85%E0%B6%B8%E0%B6%AD%E0%B6%9A-%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%99%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%8A%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%8F|title=Sunil sir made me forget who I am|newspaper=[[Silumina]] |date= 22 June 2019|accessdate=22 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dailymirror.lk/print/news-features/Sudu-andagena-kalu-awidin-99-episodes-of-reality/131-174995|title=Sudu andagena kalu awidin\u2019 99 episodes of reality|newspaper=[[The Daily Mirror (Sri Lanka)|The Daily Mirror]] |date=24 September 2019 |accessdate=24 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/news/2019/10/31/11657/%E0%B7%84%E0%B7%9C%E0%B6%B3-%E0%B6%AF%E0%B7%9A-%E0%B6%A2%E0%B6%B1%E0%B6%B4%E0%B7%8A%E2%80%8D%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%BA%E0%B6%BA%E0%B7%92|title=Best things are popular|newspaper=[[Sarasaviya]]|language=Sinhala|date=31 Oct 2019|accessdate=31 Oct 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Sumathi Award winners 2019 |url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/news-features/2019/10/31/11638/2019-\u0dc3\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dad\u0dd2-\u0dc3\u0db8\u0dca\u0db8\u0dcf\u0db1|publisher=Sarasaviya}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://epaper.resa.lk/2019/12/10/pg08_2.jpg|title=Sudu andagena kalu awidin a teledrama which gives a new path to amateur actors |newspaper=Resa |date=11 Dec 2019 |accessdate=11 Dec 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019 Dilhara was casted for the television series Haratha Hera ( King of Hearts ), aired in [[Independent Television Network]] and directed by Chandika Wijayasena. Dilhara plays the role of a wealthy girl named Pabasara, who is the only daughter of a well known Minister. After completing her higher studies she returns from abroad and re-unites with her friends. But her sole intention is to get everyone to work with her father. The overall story talks about the damage caused due to black money and how people are deliberately fallen into the business of black money.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/teledramas/2019/02/21/3078/%E0%B6%A0%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%AF%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%9A%E0%B6%BD%E0%B7%8F-%E0%B6%AF%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%AF%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%8A-%E0%B7%84%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%BB%E0%B6%AD-%E0%B7%84%E0%B7%9A%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%A7-%E0%B6%85%E0%B6%AD-%E0%B6%AD%E0%B6%B6%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%92|title=Two Chandika's started Haratha Hera|newspaper=[[Sarasaviya]]|language=Sinhala|date=21 February 2019|accessdate=21 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dailynews.lk/2019/03/12/entertainment/179923/matters-heart|title=Matters of the heart |newspaper=[[Daily News (Sri Lanka)|Daily News]] |date=12 March 2019 |accessdate=12 December 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dinamina.lk/2019/02/26/%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%92%E0%B7%81%E0%B7%9A%E0%B7%82%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%82%E0%B6%9C/69483/%E0%B6%85%E0%B6%AF-%E0%B6%A7%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%BD%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%A7%E0%B7%8A%E2%80%8D%E0%B6%BA%E0%B6%9A%E0%B6%BD%E0%B7%8F%E0%B7%80-%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%BA%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%9A-%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%B1%E0%B6%B8-%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%90%E0%B6%B1%E0%B6%9A |title=Today the teledrama industry is going on a wrong direction|publisher=[[Dinamina]]|language=Sinhala|date=26 February 2019|accessdate=26 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.silumina.lk/2019/05/11/%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%83%E0%B6%B3%E0%B7%94%E0%B6%B1/%E0%B6%AD%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%94-%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%9C%E0%B6%BB%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%94%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%94|title=Two Chandika's started Haratha Hera|newspaper=[[Silumina]] |date=14 October 2018 |accessdate=14 October 2018 }}</ref>\n\n'''Hosting Swarnavahini Weekend Vinode'''\nMichelle Dilhara hosted Weekend Vinode Entertainment television program series along with Uditha Abeyrathne and Rukshana Dissanayake aired every Saturday on [[Swarnawahini]]. The program was tended to showcase the singing, dancing and entertainment competitions between a group of audiences that changes every week. Selected people from the audience are allowed to participate in the singing, dancing and other competitions and the winners get a cash prize every week. The program featured singing artists who appeared every week to perform their solos and to entertain the audience.<ref name=\"Mawbima\"/>\n\n==Filmography==\n{{main|Michelle Dilhara filmography}}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n\n<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.silumina.lk/2018/12/29/%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%83%E0%B6%B3%E0%B7%94%E0%B6%B1/%E0%B7%83%E0%B6%B8%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%A2-%E0%B7%83%E0%B7%9A%E0%B7%80%E0%B6%BA-%E0%B6%9A%E0%B6%BB%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%9A-%E0%B6%BA%E0%B6%A7%E0%B7%92-%E0%B6%85%E0%B6%BB%C2%AD%E0%B6%B8%E0%B7%94%C2%AD%E0%B6%AB%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%8A-%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%B8%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%BA%E0%B7%92 |title=I don't expect anything from social service|newspaper=[[Silumina]] |date=29 December 2018  |accessdate=29 December 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.navaliya.com/2018/12/24/navaindex.htm|title=Young generation can change the world |date=24 December 2018|publisher=[[Navaliya]]|accessdate=24 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/features/2018/12/20/1773/%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%85-%E0%B7%84%E0%B7%9C%E0%B6%B3%E0%B6%A7-%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%85-%E0%B7%84%E0%B7%9C%E0%B6%B3%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%8A|title=Appreciation for what have done|newspaper=[[Sarasaviya]]|language=Sinhala|date=20 December 2016|accessdate=20 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.saaravita.lk/latest_news/638461/%e0%b6%b8%e0%b7%92%e0%b7%82%e0%b7%99%e0%b6%bd%e0%b7%8a%e0%b6%a7-%e0%b6%ad%e0%b7%80%e0%b6%ad%e0%b7%8a-%e0%b7%83%e0%b6%b8%e0%b7%8a%e0%b6%b8%e0%b7%8f%e0%b6%b1%e0%b6%ba%e0%b6%9a%e0%b7%8a|title=Michelle receives another award|date=2 October 2019|publisher=Saaravita|accessdate=2 October 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Raigam Tele111\">{{cite web|url=http://divaina.com/daily/index.php/welanda/39892-27-38|title=Raigam Tele'es releases the list of award nominees|date=4 March 2020|publisher=[[Divaina]]|accessdate=4 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.sundayobserver.lk/2020/03/08/business/raigam-tele%E2%80%99es-nominees-evening-mobitel|title=Raigam Tele\u2019es Nominees Evening with Mobitel|newspaper=[[Sunday Observer (Sri Lanka)|Sunday Observer]] |date=20 March 2020 |accessdate=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! width=5%| Year\n! style=\"width:25%;\"| Award\n! style=\"width:25%;\"| Award Festival\n! style=\"width:25%;\"| Category\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Result\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"  | 2018\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"  | [[Asia Inspiration Award]] \n| style=\"text-align:center;\"  | South Asian Youth Summit\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | Philanthropy \n|{{won}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"  | 2019\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"  | [[National Youth Icon Award]]  \n| style=\"text-align:center;\"  | World Youth Summit \n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | Philanthropy \n|{{won}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"  | 2019\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"  | Youth Peace Ambassador of the year 2019 \n| style=\"text-align:center;\"  | Dr.Abdul Kalam Memorial Excellence awards \n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | Philanthropy \n|{{won}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"  | 2020\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"  | [[Raigam Tele'es Best Upcoming Teledrama Actress Award|Best Upcoming Actress]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"  | [[Raigam Tele'es]] \n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | Teledrama Best Upcoming Actress\n|{{nom}}\n|}\n\n==Books==\n\n* Social Invisibility is not a Fiction it Exists 2019<ref>{{cite web |url=https://mawbima.lk/sunday-mawbima/10/sundaymawbima-more/3487|title=Michelle was loved by her fans in Kandy|publisher=[[Mawbima]]|language=Sinhala|date=15 September 2019|accessdate=15 September 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"hirufm123\">{{cite news |url=http://gossip.hirufm.lk/37497/2019/09/michel-dilhara.html#|title=I will maintain the love of my fans|newspaper=[[Hiru FM]] |date=20 September 2019 |accessdate=20 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n*[[List of Sri Lankan actors and actresses]]\n*[[Michelle Dilhara filmography]]\n*[[The invisible to visible movement]]\n*[[List of philanthropists]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.michelledilhara.com}}\n* {{facebook|100009056357717}}\n* {{IMDb name|9450804}}\n* {{Instagram|michelledilhara}}\n* [https://www.amazon.com/Social-Invisibility-Not-Fiction-Exists-ebook/dp/B07XWRGQH5 Michelle Dilhara on [[Amazon Kindle]]]\n* [http://www.sarasaviya.lk/interviews/2020/03/12/17168/\u0db8\u0dd2\u0dc2\u0dd9\u0dbd\u0dca-\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dcf \u0db8\u0d82 \u0dbb\u0d9f\u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dcf \u0dbd\u0dd0\u0db6\u0dd9\u0db1 \u0db8\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dba\u0da7 \u0dc4\u0dd0\u0da7\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dc3\u0db8\u0dcf\u0da2 \u0dc3\u0dda\u0dc0\u0dba \u0dc3\u0db3\u0dc4\u0dcf \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dcf]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=49jwdazCqfQ/ \u0dc3\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dd9\u0dc4\u0dc3\u0dca \u0d85\u0dbb\u0dab \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1 Michelle Dilhara \u0db8\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dbb\u0da7 \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd6 \u0d9a\u0dad\u0dcf\u0dc0 [[Ada Derana]]]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{Michelle Dilhara|state=collapsed}}\n{{Sinhala cinema|state=collapsed}}\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dilhara, Michelle}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sri Lankan actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century Sri Lankan actresses]]\n[[Category:Sri Lankan film actresses]]\n[[Category:Sri Lankan television actresses]]\n[[Category:Sinhalese actresses]]\n[[Category:Sri Lankan female models]]\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Sri Lankan philanthropists]]\n[[Category:People from Gampaha District]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{EngvarB|date=November 2017}}\n{{short description|Sri Lankan actress, author , social activist and philanthropist}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Michelle Dilhara\n| image        = \n| image_size   = \n| caption      = Michelle Dilhara \n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1996|5|1}}\n| birth_place  = [[Ragama]], [[Western Province, Sri Lanka|Western]], Sri Lanka\n| occupation   = Actress, author,singer, [[social activist]] ,[[philanthropist]]\n| known_for    = ''[[Salsapuna]], [[Sidu (Malee 3)]]''\n| othername    = Podi Patharakari\n| height       = 5 ft 5 in (1.65m)\n| awards       = {{flatlist|\n* [[Asia Inspiration Award]] \n* [[National Youth Icon Award]] \n* Youth Peace Ambassador of the year 2019\n}}\n| nationality  = Sri Lankan\n| spouse       = \n| children     = \n| notable_works = Social Invisibility is not a Fiction it Exists\n| parents      = H.Premawardena , E.Jean Stella Fernando\n| signature    = \n| years active = 2016\n| website      = {{URL|michelledilhara.com}}\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n | background = solo_singer\n | alias =\n | origin = Sri Lanka\n | genre = {{flatlist|\n* [[Acoustic music]]\n* pop\n* [[jazz]]\n* [[soul blues]]\n}}\n | instrument = Vocals\n | associated_acts =\n\n}}\n}}\n{{Michelle Dilhara series}}\n'''Michelle Dilhara''' ([[Sinhalese language|Sinhala]]:\u0db8\u0dd2\u0dc2\u0dd9\u0dbd\u0dca \u0daf\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dcf; born 1 May 1996)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/birthday/2019-05-01-000000/%E0%B6%BB%E0%B6%82%E0%B6%9C%E0%B6%B1-%E0%B7%81%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%BD%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%B4%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%93-%E0%B6%B8%E0%B7%92%E0%B7%82%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%BD%E0%B7%8A-%E0%B6%AF%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%BD%E0%B7%8A%E0%B7%84%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%8F|title=Actress Michelle dilhara|newspaper=[[Sarasaviya]]|language=Sinhala|date=25 April 2019|accessdate=25 April 2019}}</ref> is a Sri Lankan actress, author, philanthropist, singer and  environmental activist.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.silumina.lk/2019/03/16/%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%83%E0%B6%B3%E0%B7%94%E0%B6%B1/%E0%B6%AD%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%94-%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%9C%E0%B6%BB%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%94%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%94|title=A request letter that Michelle received|newspaper=[[Silumina]] |date= 20 April 2019|accessdate=20 April 2019}}</ref> In 2018 she won the [[Asia Inspiration Award]] at the South Asian Youth Summit held in Colombo for her contribution towards [[Social invisibility]]. Michelle received the award from the [[Minister of Youth and Sports (Malaysia)|Minister of Youth and Sports]] government of [[Malaysia]] , Mr.[[Syed Saddiq]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://divaina.com/sunday/index.php/mee/33-atambula-9/7237-2018-12-06-09-33-13|title=Michelle Receives an International award Podipatharakari has come a long way|newspaper=[[Divaina]] |date=9 December 2018 |accessdate=9 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.sundayobserver.lk/2018/12/09/news/michelle-dilhara-wins-asia-inspiration-award-2018|title=Michelle Dilhara wins Asia Inspiration Award 2018|newspaper=[[Sunday Observer (Sri Lanka)|Sunday Observer]] |date=9 December 2018 |accessdate=9 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://gossip.hirufm.lk/28385/2018/12/michelle-dilhara.html|title=Beautiful Michelle The philanthropist receives an International Award|publisher=[[Hiru TV]] |date=7 December 2018 |accessdate=7 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.citizen.lk/%E0%B6%AF%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%94%E0%B6%AB%E0%B7%94-%E0%B6%86%E0%B7%83%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%BA%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%94-%E0%B6%AD%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%94%E0%B6%AB-%E0%B7%83%E0%B6%B8%E0%B7%94%E0%B7%85%E0%B7%94/|title=Actress Michelle Dilhara receives an International Award at the South Asian Youth Summit|date=5 December 2018|publisher=Citizen|accessdate=5 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://iyc-hq.org/actor-michelle-appointed-as-iyc-deputy-ambassador-to-sri-lanka/|title=Actor Michelle appointed as IYC Deputy Ambassador to Sri Lanka|publisher=IYC headquarters New Delhi |date=15 October 2018|accessdate=22 December 2018}}</ref> She became popular as [[Podi Patharakari]] ([[Sinhalese language|Sinhala]]:\u0db4\u0ddc\u0da9\u0dd2 \u0db4\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dd3) in the teledrama, ''[[Salsapuna]]'' and as Ayoma in [[Sudu andagena kalu awidin]] aired in [[Sri Lanka Rupavahini Corporation]]<ref name=\"DN2017\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rivira.lk/online/2017/10/28/130714 |title=We will not stop the journey \u2013 Michelle Dilhara|publisher=Rivira|language=Sinhala|date=28 October 2016|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dailynews.lk/2017/12/19/features/137665/sankid-brings-seasonal-cheers |title=Sankid brings seasonal CHEERS |newspaper=[[Daily News (Sri Lanka)|Daily News]] |date=19 December 2017 |accessdate=19 December 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"ceylontoday.lk\">{{cite news |url=http://www.ceylontoday.lk/feature/2/features-more/435 |title=Michelle Dilhara A blend of altruism and talent|newspaper=[[Ceylon Today]] |date=20 May 2018 |accessdate=20 May 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"I like to become a Film Actress\">{{cite news |url=http://www.silumina.lk/2018/01/06/%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%83%E0%B6%B3%E0%B7%94%E0%B6%B1/%E0%B7%83%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%B1%E0%B6%B8%E0%B7%8F-%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%B8%E0%B7%8F%C2%AD%E0%B6%AB%C2%AD%E0%B6%BA%E0%B6%9A-%E0%B6%BB%E0%B6%9F%C2%AD%E0%B6%B4%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%B1-%E0%B6%86%E0%B7%83%E0%B6%BA%E0%B7%92 |title=I like to become a Film Actress |newspaper=[[Silumina]] |date=6 January 2018 |accessdate=6 January 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.michelledilhara.com/|title=Michelle Dilhara|website=Michelle Dilhara|accessdate=10 August 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://divaina.com/sunday/index.php/mee/33-atambula-9/9951-2019-05-24-09-23-83|title=Michelle likes to wear boots |newspaper=[[Divaina]] |date=6 May 2019|accessdate=6 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://gossip.hirufm.lk/33595/2019/06/michelle-dilhara.html|title=Everybody wants to be beautiful but I have been careful with fashion|newspaper=[[Hiru FM]] |date=1 May 2019 |accessdate=1 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://mawbima.lk/sunday-mawbima/10/sundaymawbima-more/4924|title=Christmas memories|newspaper=[[Mawbima]] |date=22 Dec 2019 |accessdate=22 Dec 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://24.siyathafm.lk/fb-recodes-of-sl-actress/|title=Beautiful actresses in Sri Lanka|publisher=[[Siyatha FM]] |date=19 July 2019 |accessdate=19 July 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019 she received the [[National Youth Icon Award]] 2019 at the World Youth Summit held in [[New Delhi]], [[India]] for her book Social Invisibility is not a Fiction it Exists and for her theory, Theory of Alternative Social Cogwheel.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://gossip.hirufm.lk/37916/2019/10/michelle-dilhara.html|title=Popular actress Michelle Dilhara receives an International Award again|publisher=[[Hiru TV]] |date=2 October 2019 |accessdate=2 October 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Alternative123\"/><ref name=\"ceylontoday11\"/><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.deshaya.lk/article/52/%E0%B7%84%E0%B6%AF%E0%B7%83%E0%B6%BB/13968/%E0%B6%86%E0%B6%AD%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%9C%E0%B7%9A-%E0%B6%A2%E0%B7%93%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%AD%E0%B6%BA-%E0%B6%85%E0%B7%83%E0%B7%8A%E0%B7%83%E0%B7%9A-%E0%B6%B8%E0%B6%B8%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%8A--%E0%B6%89%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%8F---|title=My life is also like Arthur Fleck's in Joker Film|newspaper=Deshaya|date=8 May 2019  |accessdate=8 Dec 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2020 she was nominated as the [[Raigam Tele'es Best Upcoming Teledrama Actress Award|Best Upcoming Actress]] of the year 2019 in the [[Raigam Tele'es]] award ceremony.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/teledramas/2020/03/05/16854/%E0%B6%BB%E0%B6%BA%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%9C%E0%B6%B8%E0%B7%8A-%E0%B6%A7%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%BD%E0%B7%93%E0%B7%83%E0%B7%8A-%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%AF%E0%B7%9A%E0%B7%81-%E0%B6%B8%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%B1|title=Raigam Tele'es  award nominees|date=5 March 2020|publisher=Sarasaviya|accessdate=5 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\n\nDilhara was born on 1 May 1996 in [[Ragama]], [[Sri Lanka]], to H.Premawardena, who is a businessman and E.Jean Stella Fernando. She has two sisters, Mishen Prasadika and Rochelle Fiona. Dilhara studied in Negombo South International School until her GCE Ordinary Level, which she sat as a private candidate. At the age of 11 she started practicing Martial Arts, Katate-do-Shitokai, under Sensei Rohan P. Udayakumara (Black belt dan 5). During her training, she participated for several local and international Karate championships and won medals. She won the gold medal for the 2nd International Gojuryu Karate Open Championship, conducted by the International Gojuryu Karate Association (IGKA). Meanwhile, she started volunteering as an English teacher for several children homes after an incident that took place when she was 15 years old. This made her in wanting to become a humanitarian and an actress. Dilhara completed her GCE Advanced Level in Arts Stream ( English Literature, Japanese Language and IT ) at [[Newstead Girls College]] [[Negombo]]. There she was able to participate in several dramas conducted by the school drama team, that gave her the first experience in taking part in a play. In 2013 she also completed her Japanese Language Proficiency Test ( JLPT N5 and N4 ) which was conducted by the Japanese Language Education Association of Sasakawa Centre [[Sri Lanka]].<ref name=\"Fernando\">{{cite news |url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/170827/magazine/an-actress-in-search-of-recognition-instead-of-popularity-255830.html |title=An actress in search of recognition instead of popularity |newspaper=[[Sunday Times (Sri Lanka)|Sunday Times]] |first=Susitha R. |last=Fernando |date=27 August 2017 |accessdate=27 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://fragmenteyes.blogspot.com/2017/11/michelle-dilhara-acting-on-moving-on.html|title=Michelle Dilhara: Acting on, moving on|newspaper=Fragmentes|date=10 January 2019 |accessdate=10 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.deshaya.lk/article/52/%E0%B7%84%E0%B6%AF%E0%B7%83%E0%B6%BB/8601/%E0%B6%B4%E0%B7%94%E0%B6%82%E0%B6%A0%E0%B7%92-%E0%B6%B4%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%AD%E0%B6%BB%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%A7-%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%B8-%E0%B6%B4%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%B8%E0%B7%8A%E0%B7%80%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%8A-%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%90%E0%B7%84%E0%B7%90|title=Podi Patharakari still don't have a boyfriend|newspaper=Deshaya|language=Sinhala|date=22 September 2018|accessdate=22 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nAt the age of fifteen, an incident changed her life. While she was visiting her uncle at the Negombo Hospital with her father, she witnessed a fight between a family and the hospital staff members about discharging a dead body. The incident caught the attention of the people around as well as hers. After about an hour when she returned with her father, she saw that one body was taken and the other was still lying. After few weeks when she revisited her uncle, she got to know from the hospital staff that nobody came to claim the other body since, so that they had buried it with government funds. \nThis occurrence made her think that even though the two dead individuals were from the same town, same country and died in the same period of time, they had two different destinies. According to Dilhara, there are people who are treated differently, neglected and marginalized in the society such as elderly, homeless people, people with disability who are being invisible to the public. She, who was also a victim of social invisibility during this period of time, decided to speak on behalf of other socially invisible individuals by looking into their needs.<ref name=\"dailynews222\"/>\n\nDilhara joined Abhina Academy conducted by the veteran actress [[Anoja Weerasinghe]]. Anoja became her first acting guru. In an interview published in ''[[Sunday Observer]]'' and ''[[Daily News (Sri Lanka)|Daily News]]'', Dilhara said that [[Anoja Weerasinghe]] taught the basic principals of acting with meditation and yoga that helped her build voice control and facial expressions. Later she joined Damayanthi Fonseka's acting Academy to study emotional balancing and character adaptation. Dilhara also studied Drama and Theatre at Abhiranga Art Centre Negombo, conducted by Randika Wimalasooriya. During this period, she got the opportunity to study Art from the Indian Theatre Director, Ujjwal Singha. Dilhara stated that Ujjwal got her through the Indian Theatre and Children's theatre that helped her to open up perspectives in overseas too. Apart from acting, Dilhara is currently studying for an External Degree in IT and a Diploma course in Psychology.<ref name=\"DN2017\">{{cite news |url=http://dailynews.lk/2017/10/10/features/130673/be-difference |title=Be the difference |newspaper=[[Daily News (Sri Lanka)|Daily News]] |date=10 October 2017 |accessdate=27 November 2017}}</ref> She is also following a course on Nurturing Care Framework for Early Chilhood Development with the Senior Lecturer Mr.Duminda Guruge, at the Rajarata University of Sri Lanka.<ref name=\"dailynews222\">{{cite news |url=http://www.dailynews.lk/2019/01/10/tc/173752/inspiring-act |title=An inspiring 'act'!|newspaper=[[Daily News (Sri Lanka)|Daily News]] |date=10 January 2019 |accessdate=10 January 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"CT2017\">{{cite news|url=https://ceylontoday.lk/print20170401CT20170630.php?id=34970|title=Living the Dream|newspaper=Ceylon Today|date=26 November 2017|first=Milan|last=Lu|accessdate=27 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://sarasaviya.lk/2017/03/23/?fn=sa1703233 |title=It is important to act more actively than to become more popular|newspaper=[[Sarasaviya]]|language=Sinhala|date=16 March 2016|accessdate=27 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.saaravita.lk/travel/516279/%E0%B6%A2%E0%B6%B1%E0%B6%B4%E2%80%8D%E0%B7%8A%E2%80%8D%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%BA-%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%B1-%E0%B6%B8%E0%B6%A7-%E0%B6%95%E0%B6%B1%E0%B6%9A%E0%B6%B8%E0%B6%9A|title=I Don't Want to be Famous|date=16 April 2017|publisher=Saaravita|accessdate=16 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Philanthropy ==\n\n==Awards==\nDilhara won the Asia Inspiration Award 2018 for the category of philanthropy at the second South Asian Youth Summit held in Colombo. Michelle Dilhara received the award from [[Minister of Youth and Sports (Malaysia)|Minister of Youth and Sports]] government of [[Malaysia]] , [[Syed Saddiq]] for the philanthropic work involved with [[Social invisibility]]. The event was organized by the International Youth Committee (IYC), an organization that supports the youth around the world.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dailynews.lk/2018/09/18/local/162912/south-asian-youth-summit-be-held-colombo |title=South Asian Youth Summit to be held in Colombo|newspaper=[[Daily News (Sri Lanka)|Daily News]] |date=18 September 2018 |accessdate=18 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.colombopage.com/archive_18B/Sep23_1537674160CH.php|title= Sri Lanka to host South Asian Youth Summit 2018 |newspaper=Colombopage|date=23 September 2018 |accessdate=23 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.island.lk/index.php?page_cat=article-details&page=article-details&code_title=191694|title=Lanka hosts South Asian Youth Summit|newspaper=[[The Island (Sri Lanka)|The Island]] |date=18 September 2018 |accessdate=18 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.colombopage.com/archive_18B/Sep23_1537674160CH.php|title= Sri Lanka to host South Asian Youth Summit 2018 |newspaper=Colombopage|date=23 September 2018 |accessdate=23 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thedailystar.net/city/news/sri-lanka-host-2nd-south-asian-youth-summit-1637302|title= 2nd South Asian Youth Summit in Sri Lanka|newspaper=The Daily Star |date=23 September 2018 |accessdate=23 September 2018}}</ref> IYC chooses 30 youth from Asia who would be the next leaders in Asia. Over 450 delegates from more than 80 countries, including the SAARC observer nations, took part in the event. Dilhara was into social welfare since she was teenager. In an interview published in the ''[[Daily News (Sri Lanka)|Daily News]]'', she said that she is happy if she can help someone smlie, share a few kind words, or lend a helping hand to those who need.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mawbima.lk/article20171001MB20180331.php?id=9781|title=Shining star Michel receives an international award for philanthropy|publisher=[[Mawbima]]|language=Sinhala|date=12 December 2018|accessdate=12 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://sundayobserver.lk/2018/12/16/youth-observer/mesmerising-michelle|title=Mesmerising Michelle|publisher=[[Sunday Observer (Sri Lanka)|Sunday Observer]]|date=16 December 2018|accessdate=16 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n{{quote box\n |title = \n |quote = {{font|font=Times New Roman|size=large|''\"Social Invisibility is not a fiction it exists\"''}}\n|source = \u2014 Michelle Dilhara quotes <ref name=\"ceylontoday123\"/><ref name=\"sundayobserver123\"/><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.globestats.com/most-famous-quotes-of-all-time/|title=Most Famous Quotes of All Time|publisher=Globestats|date=5 Dec 2019|accessdate=5 Dec 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.openthenews.com/the-100-most-famous-quotes-of-all-time/|title=The 100 Most Famous Quotes of All Time|publisher=Openthenews|date=5 Dec 2019|accessdate=5 Dec 2019}}</ref>\n |align = right  |width = 35%  |border = 1px  |fontsize = 100%  |bgcolor = #f0f0ff  |title_bg = #f0f0ff  |title_fnt = #202060  \n|qalign = left \n|salign = right\n}}\n\nDilhara won the Naional Youth Icon Award 2019 at the World Youth Summit held in [[New Delhi]], [[India]] for the book she wrote Social Invisibility is not a Fiction it Exists and for her theory, Theory of Alternative Social Cogwheel. She received the award from Dr.Jayantha Patra the Chairman of the International Youth Committee ( IYC ). The World Youth Summit focuses on [[Poverty eradication]], Food and Nutrition Security, Conservation of Biodiversity for Sustainability, Disaster Risk Reductions and Youth Cantered Urbanization, [[Ecotourism]] Development, Preservation of Indigenous People and Our Heritage, Realizing Equal Access to Quality Education and Health, . The award ceremony and the summit was taken place at the Dr Ambedkar International Centre, [[New Delhi]].<ref name=\"Alternative123\"/><ref name=\"ceylontoday11\"/>\n\nIn 2020 she was nominated as the Best Up-coming Teledrama Actress of the year 2019 in the Raigam Tele'es award ceremony for her performance as Ayoma in the teledrama Sudu Andagena Kalu Awidin, aired in the Sri Lanka Rupavahini Corporation.<ref name=\"Raigam Tele111\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.raigamtelees.lk/awards/nominees|title=Nomination List Raigam Tele'es 2019 |date=5 March 2020|publisher=[[Raigam Tele'es]]|accessdate=5 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Activism==\nShe was a voluntary English teacher for many child orphanages in [[Sri Lanka]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://old.lankadeepa.lk/index.php/articles/590465 |title=Podipatharakari is a teacher|publisher=[[Lankadeepa]]|language=Sinhala|date=28 March 2018|accessdate=28 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://admin.lankadeepa.lk/index.php/articles/548091 |title=Love is a very profound subject|publisher=[[Lankadeepa]]|language=Sinhala|date=27 November 2017|accessdate=27 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.navaliya.com/2018/06/04/New%20folder/a3.jpg|title=I always try to do something good |date=4 June 2018|publisher=[[Navaliya]]|accessdate=4 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.saaravita.lk/latest_news/590465/%E0%B6%B4%E0%B7%9C%E0%B6%A9%E0%B7%92-%E0%B6%B4%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%AD%E0%B6%BB%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%92-%E0%B6%AF%E0%B7%90%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%8A-%E0%B6%9C%E0%B7%94%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%94%E0%B7%80%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%BA%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%8A|title=Podipatharakari is now a teacher |date=24 September 2018|publisher=Saaravita|accessdate=24 September 2018}}</ref> After she became an actress, there were many pictures of Dilhara in magazines participating in many occasions in luxurious hotels in Sri Lanka. One day a small child in the orphanage had asked her about the luxurious hotels after seeing these magazines. The child said that she will never be able to go to a hotel like this ever. Dilhara invited this child with all her friends in the orphanage to the Cinnamon Grand Hotel [[Sri Lanka]] for her 21st birthday.<ref name=\"ceylontoday.lk\"/>\n\nIn 2016 Michelle organized a campaign with Manusha D. Navarathna, an active environmental activist,  to reduce the Environmental Degradation with regard to [[Climate change]]. Dilhara believed that plastic is one of the main objects that affects [[Climate change]]. The campaign was taken place at the [[Negombo]] beach premises for three consecutive days to remove all the plastic objects that were circling in the beach. They were able to remove plastic bottles, trash, plastic bags and other objects that would pollute the environment.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rivira.lk/online/2018/06/09/151570 |title=If you do the right thing you will get the right result \u2013 Michelle Dilhara|publisher=Rivira|language=Sinhala|date=23 June 2018|accessdate=23 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2017, Dilhara and Manusha D. Navarathna organized a project to plant 1000 trees as a solution to minimize the ongoing [[Climate crisis]] taken place due to [[Global warming]] and [[Climate change]]. The trees were planted in [[Katana]],[[Gampaha]] District of [[Sri Lanka]].<ref name=\"Michelle Dilhara B'day Celebration\">{{cite web |url=http://admin.lankadeepa.lk/index.php/articles/520638 |title=Michelle Dilhara B'day Celebration|publisher=[[Lankadeepa]]|language=Sinhala|date=15 October 2018|accessdate=15 October 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017 she wanted to change the focus of the youngsters to support poor to stand on their feet rather than wasting time on video games. She had a vision that if one person supports a poor person, with a kilo of rice, there will be at least 20 million kilos of rice for the poor. She organized a campaign for her 22nd birthday and she was able to get the support of more than one thousand youngsters for this project. They collected more than one thousand kilos of rice and gave them to the needy in Pinnakalewattha village.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://divaina.com/sunday/index.php/mee/33-atambula-9/3723-24-12 |title=Salsapuna Podipatharakari celebrates the birthday differently|newspaper=[[Divaina]] |date=13 May 2018 |accessdate=13 May 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Michelle Dilhara B'day Celebration\"/>\n\nIn January 2020, Michelle Dilhara conducted multiple awareness programs on [[Climate change]] and [[Social invisibility]] in [[Rajarata University of Sri Lanka]], schools, television programmes, talk shows, and on several national newspapers.<ref name=\"Alternative123\"/><ref name=\"ceylontoday11\"/>\n\n==Quotes==\n{{wikiquote|Michelle Dilhara}}\n<blockquote> \"Social Invisibility is not a fiction it exists\" <ref name=\"ceylontoday123\"/><ref name=\"sundayobserver123\"/><ref name=\"themorningherald.com\">{{cite web|url=http://themorningherald.com/news/the-invisible-to-visible-movement-founded-by-michelle-dilhara/0193021|title=The Invisible to Visible movement founded by Michelle Dilhara|date=17 Nov 2019|newspaper=[[The Morning Herald]]|accessdate=17 Nov 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goodreads.com/quotes/tag/michelle-dilhara-quotes|title=Michelle Dilhara Quotes|date=6 Dec 2019|newspaper=[[Goodreads]]|accessdate=6 Dec 2019}}</ref></blockquote>\n\n==The invisible to visible movement==\n{{further|The invisible to visible movement}}\nIn 2018 Michelle initiated \" The invisible to visible movement \" for the people who are afftected by [[Social invisibility]] and [[Social exclusion]] .Michelle promoted Social invisibility in an interview published in [[Ceylon Today]] and [[Sunday Observer (Sri Lanka)]]. Dilhara said that Social Invisibility is Not a Fiction, it Exists.<ref name=\"ceylontoday123\">{{cite news|url=http://ceylontoday.lk/feature/8/features-more/2828|title=Social Invisibility is Not a Fiction, it Exists|newspaper=[[Ceylon Today]]|date=25 May 2019|first=Michelle |last=Dilhara|accessdate=25 May 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"digitaljournal222\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.digitaljournal.com/pr/4485900|title=Michelle Dilhara\u2019s book Social Invisibility is not fiction, projected to be one of the most influential pieces ever written|publisher=Digital Journal|date=26 October 2019|accessdate=26 October 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Social Invisibility\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bignewsnetwork.com/news/262993122/the-invisible-to-visible-movement-founded-by-michelle-dilhara|title=The Invisible to Visible movement founded by Michelle Dilhara|date=17 Nov 2019|newspaper=[[Big News Network]]|accessdate=17 Nov 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"sundayobserver123\">{{cite news |url=http://www.sundayobserver.lk/2019/06/02/youth-observer/social-invisibility-not-fiction-it-exists|title=Social invisibility is not fiction, it exists|newspaper=[[Sunday Observer (Sri Lanka)|Sunday Observer]] |date=2 June 2019 |accessdate=2 June 2019}}</ref> In an interview given to [[Fox 34]] ,[[Hiru FM]],[[NBC 29]] ,[[Tulsa CW]] and [[Ceylon Today]] Michelle said that she started a free English scholarship program for the financially challenged  students in [[Sri Lanka]] with the support of the English lecturer Danushka Clark.<ref name=\"ceylontoday11\">{{cite news|url=https://ceylontoday.lk/features-more/4150|title=Through the Eyes of a Humanitarian|newspaper=[[Ceylon Today]]|date=11 November 2019|first=Priyangwada|last=Perera|accessdate=11 November 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"ceylontoday123\"/><ref name=\"sundayobserver123\"/><ref name=\"hirufm123\"/> At first it started with 200 students in [[Divulapitiya]] town and now it has grown up to 1000 students eventually. The scholarship programme was initiated as a sub project of The Invisible to Visible movement to minimize the [[Social invisibility]] and [[Social exclusion]]  of the people due to factors such as educational status and  [[language barrier]]. The main focus of this project is to develop their communication skills with the world and to create a path for them to approach the international job market through online jobs.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.saaravita.lk/latest_news/642492/%e0%b6%89%e0%b6%9c%e0%b7%99%e0%b6%b1%e0%b6%9c%e0%b6%b1%e0%b7%8a%e0%b6%b1-%e0%b6%ad%e0%b7%80-%e0%b7%84%e0%b7%94%e0%b6%9f%e0%b7%8f%e0%b6%9a%e0%b7%8a-%e0%b6%af%e0%b7%9a-%e0%b6%ad%e0%b7%92%e0%b6%ba|title=There is lot to learn|date=4 Nov 2019|publisher=Saaravita|accessdate=4 Nov 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"digitaljournal222\"/><ref name=\"Social Invisibility\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://epaper.themorning.lk/Home/ShareArticle?OrgId=d4ac636c&imageview=0|title=From Invisibility to visibility with Michelle|date=17 Nov 2019|newspaper=The Morning|accessdate=17 Nov 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Social Invisibility\"/><ref name=\"themorningherald.com\"/><ref name=\"sundayobserver123\"/><ref name=\"Mawbima\">{{cite web |url=http://www.mawbima.lk/sunday-mawbima/10/sundaymawbima-more/1003|title=Sudu Andagena Kalu Avidin in sri lanka Rupavahini Corporation |publisher=[[Mawbima]]|language=Sinhala|date=23 March 2019|accessdate=23 March 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Social Invisibility\">{{Cite book|title=Social Invisibility is not a fiction it exists|isbn= 978-1692768461|publisher=Amazon}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://gossip.hirufm.lk/38304/2019/10/michel-dilhara.html|title=Cell Phone Addiction is real we eat , Brush your teeth, and sleeps with cell phone|newspaper=[[Hiru FM]] |date=13 Oct 2019|accessdate=13 Oct 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2020 Michelle founded Senehas Arana, a community center for the retired citizens who are affected from [[Social invisibility]] and [[Social exclusion]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://br-cam.com/video/49jwdazCqfQ/wanitha-waruna-michelle-dilhara.html|title=Michelle Dilhara's first interview on \"Senehas Arana\"|newspaper=[[Ada Derana]] |date=1 March 2020|accessdate=1 March 2020}}</ref> She released her first theory \"The Theory of Alternative Social Cogwheel\" for the people who are affected from [[Social invisibility]] and [[Social exclusion]]. It is a sociological theory of how people are affected due to factors such as the [[Ageism|the elderly]] ,[[disability|people with a disability]] ,[[education|educational status]] , barriers for senior citizens in getting new jobs, discrimination and violence. Michelle founded Senehas Arana as a practical implementation of her theory. The community center brings all the retired citizens who are affected with Social Invisibility and Social Exclusion in [[Divulapitiya]] area to one place, and regenerates the community networks of the affected retired citizens.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/interviews/2020/03/12/17168/%E0%B6%B8%E0%B7%92%E0%B7%82%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%BD%E0%B7%8A-%E0%B6%AF%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%BD%E0%B7%8A%E0%B7%84%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%8F|title=I'm spending sixty percent of my income for social service|date=12 March 2020|publisher=Sarasaviya|accessdate=12 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Alternative123>{{cite web|url=http://www.ft.lk/lifestyle/The-Theory-of-Alternative-Social-Cogwheel-by-Michelle-Dilhara/8-696198|title=The Theory of Alternative Social Cogwheel by Michelle Dilhara|date=24 February 2020|publisher=[[Daily FT]]|accessdate=24 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dinamina.lk/2020/03/16/%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%92%E0%B7%81%E0%B7%9A%E0%B7%82%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%82%E0%B6%9C/92326/%E0%B6%B8%E0%B6%9C%E0%B7%9A-%E0%B7%84%E0%B7%93%E0%B6%B1-%E0%B6%AF%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%9A%E0%B6%B8-%E0%B7%83%E0%B7%90%E0%B6%B6%E0%B7%91-%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%94%E0%B6%AB%E0%B7%8F|title=Both of my dreams came true|date=16 March 2020|publisher=[[Dinamina]]|accessdate=16 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aruna.lk/%e0%b7%80%e0%b7%90%e0%b6%a9%e0%b7%92%e0%b7%84%e0%b7%92%e0%b6%a7%e0%b7%92%e0%b6%ba%e0%b6%b1%e0%b7%8a-%e0%b7%80%e0%b7%99%e0%b6%b1%e0%b7%94%e0%b7%80%e0%b7%99%e0%b6%b1%e0%b7%8a-%e0%b6%a2%e0%b7%93%e0%b7%80/?fbclid=IwAR0coR-Z_zpzFOM3PozoPNxs_W7dyGCWZJazOBWkHKxzOixgLAVSkftNlro|title=I dedicate my life for elders|date=15 March 2020|newspaper=Aruna|accessdate=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://mawbima.lk/sunday-mawbima/10/sundaymawbima-more/6165|title=Michelle opens a Community centre for elders|date=15 March 2020|newspaper=[[Mawbima]]|accessdate=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://divaina.com/sunday/index.php/mee/33-atambula-9/13424-2020-02-28-03-11-69|title=Actress Michelle Dilhara opens a community center for retired elders |newspaper=[[Divaina]] |date=1 March 2020 |accessdate=1 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://gossip.hirufm.lk/43549/2020/03/michel-dilhara.html|title=I don't do social services for publicity|newspaper=[[Hiru FM]] |date=1 March 2020|accessdate=1 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.deshaya.lk/article/52/%E0%B7%84%E0%B6%AF%E0%B7%83%E0%B6%BB/13311/%E0%B6%92%E0%B6%9A-%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%A7%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%8A-%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%9C%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%9A%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%B1-%E0%B7%84%E0%B7%94%E0%B6%AF%E0%B6%9A%E0%B6%BD%E0%B7%8F%E0%B7%80%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%8A|title=No one can't understand that lonelyness|newspaper=Deshaya|language=Sinhala|date=12 Oct 2019|accessdate=12 Oct 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n\n===2016\u20132017 Career ===\nIn 2016, Dilhara made her first teledrama appearance in ''[[Salsapuna]]'' telecasted on [[Sirasa TV]]. The drama was created in a middle class environment that widely involved love triangles, plot twists, and character changes. She was auditioned for the character [[Podi Patharakari]] ([[Sinhalese language|Sinhala]]:\u0db4\u0ddc\u0da9\u0dd2 \u0db4\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dd3) in [[Salsapuna]] by Sandya Mendis, Chairman of Susila Productions. After several auditions, Dilhara was selected for the character Preethiwa, widely known to the audience as [[Podi Patharakari]]. The character was introduced in the 252nd of 577 episodes. Preethiwa [[Podi Patharakari]] is a wealthy girl who visited her mother country, after completing her higher studies in London, with the intention of learning journalism. The character [[Podi Patharakari]] was introduced as the girlfriend of the character Nilhan. She is a journalist who left her luxury life and lived an ordinary life, fighting against injustice. Dilhara said that the other cast members including Rohana Beddage and [[Damitha Abeyratne]] supported in her character portrayal. The teledrama was directed by the veteran director Nalan Mendis, who also directed Doo Daruwo, which became one of the most popular and long running teledramas in Sri Lanka and Nadayo. During the same period, she then appeared with the leading role in the first Mobile drama Dhara, produced by Susila Productions.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://navaliya.com/2017/05/22/artworld1.html |title=I meditate 20 minutes everyday |date=22 May 2017|publisher=[[Navaliya]]|accessdate=22 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.saaravita.lk/travel/548091/%E0%B6%86%E0%B6%AF%E0%B6%BB%E0%B6%BA-%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%BA%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%99-%E0%B7%84%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%92-%E0%B6%9C%E0%B7%90%E0%B6%B9%E0%B7%94%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%94-%E0%B7%80|title=Podipatharakari character was loved by everyone|date=13 May 2018|publisher=Saaravita|accessdate=13 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://starfriends.lk/%e0%b6%b8%e0%b7%92%e0%b7%82%e0%b7%99%e0%b6%bd%e0%b7%8a-%e0%b6%ba%e0%b7%9d%e0%b6%9c%e0%b7%8f-%e0%b6%9a%e0%b6%bb%e0%b6%bd%e0%b7%8f%e0%b6%bd%e0%b7%94-%e0%b6%87%e0%b6%9f-%e0%b7%84%e0%b6%af%e0%b7%8f/|title=Michelle does yoga to maintain her body|date=13 January 2018|publisher=starfriends|accessdate=13 January 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"sarasaviya.lk\">{{cite web |url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/teles/?fn=sa17100510 |title=A family that is aligned to be one family|newspaper=[[Sarasaviya]]|language=Sinhala|date=5 October 2017|accessdate=5 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dinamina.lk/2017/03/24/%E0%B6%85%E0%B6%AD%E0%B6%B1-%E0%B6%B8%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%AD%E0%B6%B1-gossip/31666 |title=Michelle Dilhara \"Salsapuna\" actress speaks|publisher=[[Dinamina]]|language=Sinhala|date=24 March 2017|accessdate=24 March 2017}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Michelle Dilhara with fans.jpg|thumb|alt=|left|Michelle Dilhara]]\n\nIn 2018 Michelle was casted for the teledrama [[Sidu (TV series)]] which was telecasted weekdays on [[TV Derana]]. The teledrama depicts the story of a 9 year old boy with wizarding powers and his friendship with a little Buddhist monk. Dilhara played a fictional character that portrayed a daylight angel who was sent by Sidu's grandmother in order save his life from danger and evil. The character revolved mainly around Sidu, played by Nethma Aakashmita, his friends and the little Buddhist monk of the village temple, Sorataha saamanera played by Kaveesh Vihanga. Only Sidu was able to visualize the Daylight Angel whenever he was in a problem. The teledrama was directed by Thilina Boralessa and written by Saman Edirimunee.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ceylontoday.lk/site-api/uploads/e_paper/GLAMOUR-20-05-2018.pdf|title=Michelle Dilhara A blend of altruism and talent|date=13 January 2018|publisher=[[Ceylon Today]]|accessdate=13 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n===2017\u20132018 Career ===\nIn 2017, Dilhara was featured in the Maliban tea advertisement with the leading role that became very popular as Maliban tea ( [[Maliban Biscuit Manufactories Limited]] ) advertisement girl among the Sri Lankan audience. In 2018 she also starred in the Maliban Tea second commercial with once again the leading role.\n\nDuring the same period, she was casted to [[Poori]] teledrama which was telecasted on [[Independent Television Network]] with 75 episodes.<ref name=\"I like to become a Film Actress\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://starfriends.lk/%E0%B6%B8%E0%B7%9A%E0%B6%B1%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%9C%E0%B7%9A-%E0%B6%85%E0%B6%BD%E0%B7%94%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%B8-%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%90%E0%B6%A9%E0%B7%9A-%E0%B6%B4%E0%B7%96%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%93/|title=Menaka's latest teledrama Poori|date=13 January 2018|publisher=starfriends|accessdate=13 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.saaravita.lk/On-location/605966/poori-teledrama-on-location|title=Poori Teledrama On-Location|date=16 April 2017|publisher=Saaravita|accessdate=16 April 2018}}</ref> The drama was directed by Ranil Kulasinghe and produced by Janaka Sampath Telemax Productions. She played the role of a village girl named Maali. The character portrays a strong and positive minded girl who doesn't care much of her personal life, but cares about others.\n\nIn the same year, Dilhara was casted for the teledrama Bodhi, directed by Sanjaya Nirmal and produced by Malathi Wijesinghe. The drama was telecated on [[Sirasa TV]]. Dilhara was chosen for the character [[Hindu goddess]] , portrayed as the demon [[Kali]].According to the Hindu folk tales, [[Kali]] is the symbol of Death or Time. Dilhara had to undergo many changes in her makeup to get the appearance of [[Kali]] such as getting her body painted in blue, making her hair fizzy, and painting her nails red.Kali is one of the different and challenging characters portrayed by Dilhara.<ref name=\"Fernando\"/>\n\n'''Hosting Sirasa TV 16+'''\nMichelle Dilhara hosted the 16+ program in [[Sirasa TV]], which was telecasted every Sundays at 5.00&nbsp;pm. 16+ is a music program targeted for the young generation conducted by sarith surith jayawardena's band, who won the poddanta puluwan contest.. singers include young singers from sirasa junior superstar and sirasa poddanta puluwan.. The director of the program is Mr. Dilan and the producers are Mr. Lahiru and Ms. Sachithra.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.lakbima.lk/index.php/gossip/13279-michelle-dilhara |title=I never had a boyfriend ,nobody ever asked me out|newspaper=[[Lakbima]] |date=9 September 2018 |accessdate=9 September 2018}}</ref><ref>http://sirasatv.lk/2018/07/09/16-2018-07-08/</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.silumina.lk/2018/06/23/%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%83%E0%B6%B3%E0%B7%94%E0%B6%B1/%E0%B6%AD%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%94-%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%BB%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%94%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%94|title=Michelle becomes a presenter |newspaper=[[Silumina]] |date=14 October 2018 |accessdate=14 October 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.saaravita.lk/latest_news/580477/%E0%B6%B4%E0%B7%9C%E0%B6%A9%E0%B7%92-%E0%B6%B4%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%AD%E0%B6%BB%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%93-%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%92%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%9A%E0%B6%AF%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%8F|title=Podi Patharakari has becomes a presenter|publisher=saaravita|language=Sinhala|date=18 July 2018|accessdate=18 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017 Dilhara appeared in the Sri Lankan television series [[Emy Teledrama]] as the leading role Emy.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://ceylontoday.lk/news-search/emy/features-more/2589|title='Emy' is on the Way|newspaper=[[Ceylon Today]] |date=29 April 2019 |accessdate=29 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mawbima.lk/sunday-mawbima/10/sundaymawbima-more/1393|title=EMY a new path to children's teledrmas.|publisher=[[Mawbima]]|language=Sinhala|date=20 April 2019|accessdate=20 April 2019}}</ref> The TV series was Directed by Sanjaya Nirmal and produced by Malathi Wijesinghe. The teledrama started airing in 2019. Dilhara plays the role of a fifteen-year-old girl named Emy, who was born and raised in UK. But due to some issues in her family and her bad health condition, she visits her grandmother in [[Sri Lanka]], portrayed by Hyacinth Wijeratne, to spend her last few months. The drama includes another five characters who have extraordinary capabilities.\n\nDilhara appeared in the teledrama [[Thuththiri]] (Sinhala: \u0dad\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd2), a Sri Lankan science fiction television series telecasted on the television network [[Sirasa TV]] .<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.asianmirror.lk/entertainment/item/26188-thuththiri-new-sinhala-mega-teledrama-to-make-way-to-small-screen-soon|title=\"Thuththiri\" New Sinhala Mega Teledrama To Make Way To Small Screen Soon |date=24 November 2017|publisher=Asianmirror|accessdate=24 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.silumina.lk/2017/11/11/%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%83%E0%B6%B3%E0%B7%94%E0%B6%B1/%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%94%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%92-%E0%B7%85%E0%B6%9F%E0%B6%AF%E0%B7%93%E0%B6%B8-%E0%B6%B4%E0%B7%94%E0%B6%82%E0%B6%A0%E0%B7%92-%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%BB%E0%B6%BA%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%8A |title=Thuththiri will telecast soon|newspaper=[[Silumina]] |date=11 November 2017  |accessdate=11 November 2017 }}</ref><ref name=\"sarasaviya.lk\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dinamina.lk/2018/08/14/%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%92%E0%B7%81%E0%B7%9A%E0%B7%82%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%82%E0%B6%9C/58517/%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%83%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%9A%E0%B6%BA%E0%B7%8F-%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%83%E0%B7%8A-%E0%B6%AF%E0%B7%9A%E0%B7%80%E0%B6%BD%E0%B7%8A-%E0%B6%B4%E0%B7%92%E0%B7%85%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%9C%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%8F|title=Fans expect different concepts|publisher=[[Dinamina]]|language=Sinhala|date=14 March 2018|accessdate=14 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://mirrorarts.lk/news/2252-thuththiri-tele|title=Thuththiri for Television |publisher=mirrorarts|language=Sinhala|date=19 November 2017|accessdate=19 November 2017}}</ref> Michelle played the role of an alien named \"Urmila\". The story is based on a mythical belief that people will one day live under thuththiri plants in future. The drama begins with the invasion of a group of aliens to the earth, starring Michelle Dilhara, Morin Charuni, Kavinga Perera and Jake Senaratna. It was produced by U.A.Palliyaguru, who was also the producer for the films Super Six and Pani Makuluwo, and directed by Sanjaya Nirmal. The drama was also considered to be the first Sifi Comedy mega drama.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://menafn.com/1095947111/Young-Lankan-actress-Michelle-Dilhara-seeks-immortality-but-for-others-sake |title=Young Lankan actress Michelle Dilhara seeks immortality but for others' sake|date=12 October 2017|publisher=Middle East North Africa Financial Network, Inc.|accessdate=27 November 2017}}</ref>\n\n'''Hosting 2nd South Asian Youth Summit (2018)''' \nMichelle Dilhara was the official host for the 2nd South Asian Youth Summit held in Sri Lanka. Over 450 delegates from 80 countries participated this event. She also won the Asia Inspiration Award 2018 for her contribution to the South Asian philanthropy<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dailynews.lk/2018/09/18/local/162912/south-asian-youth-summit-be-held-colombo|title=2nd South Asian Youth Summit in Sri Lanka|newspaper=[[Daily News (Sri Lanka)|Daily News]] |date=18 September 2017 |accessdate=18 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thedailystar.net/city/news/sri-lanka-host-2nd-south-asian-youth-summit-1637302|title=2nd South Asian Youth Summit in Sri Lanka|newspaper=[[The Daily Star (Bangladesh)|Daily Star]] |date=10 January 2019 |accessdate=10 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.lakbima.lk/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=15354:%E0%B6%BA%E0%B7%9C%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%94%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%8A-%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%92%E0%B7%85%E0%B7%92-%E0%B6%B8%E0%B7%92%E0%B7%82%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%BD%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%9C%E0%B7%9A-%E0%B7%83%E0%B6%B8%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%A2-%E0%B6%B8%E0%B7%99%E0%B7%84%E0%B7%99%E0%B7%80%E0%B6%BB%E0%B6%A7-%E0%B6%A2%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%8A%E2%80%8D%E0%B6%BA%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%AD%E0%B6%BB-%E0%B7%83%E0%B6%B8%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%B8%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%B1%E0%B6%BA%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%8A&catid=35:%E0%B6%9A%E0%B6%BD%E0%B7%8F-%E0%B6%B4%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%96%E0%B6%BB-%E0%B6%9C%E0%B7%90%E0%B6%BD%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%BA&Itemid=254|title=Young actress Michelle Dilhara received an award for her social work |newspaper=[[Lakbima]] |date=3 January 2019 |accessdate=3 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n===2018\u20132019 Career ===\nDilhara was casted for [[Sudu andagena kalu awidin]] aired in [[Sri Lanka Rupavahini Corporation]] , directed by Sunil Costa.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://mawbima.lk/sunday-mawbima/10/sundaymawbima-more/2352|title=Sudu Andagena Kalu Awdin created with a great difficulty|publisher=[[Mawbima]]|language=Sinhala|date=29 June 2019|accessdate=29 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://divaina.com/sunday/index.php/mee/33-atambula-9/10238-2019-05-24-09-23-137|title=I shoot Sudu andagena kalu awidin according to my concept director Sunil costa Speaks |newspaper=[[Divaina]] |date=23 June 2019 |accessdate=23 June 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Mawbima\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/teledramas/2019/03/21/3636/%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%96%E0%B6%B4%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%8F%E0%B7%84%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%BA%E0%B6%A7-%E0%B7%83%E0%B7%94%E0%B6%AF%E0%B7%94-%E0%B6%87%E0%B6%B3%E0%B6%9C%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%B1-%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%85%E0%B7%94-%E0%B6%87%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%AF%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%8A|title=Sudu Andagena Kalu Avidin in Rupavahini|newspaper=[[Sarasaviya]]|language=Sinhala|date=21 March 2019|accessdate=21 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://divaina.com/sunday/index.php/mee/33-atambula-9/9107-2019-04-03-15-07-61|title=Michelle talks about the character Ayoma in Sudu andagena kalu awidin|newspaper=[[Divaina]] |date=7 April 2019 |accessdate=7 April 2019 }}</ref> She portrays the character Ayoma, who is a teenage girl facing the hardships of life. [[Sudu andagena kalu awidin]] is Dilhara's first major role.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.resa.lk/%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%92%E0%B7%81%E0%B7%9A%E0%B7%82%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%82%E0%B6%9C/2019/may/07/10887/%E0%B6%A2%E0%B6%B1%E0%B6%BA%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%8A%E0%B7%80%E0%B6%BA-%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%90%E0%B6%9A%E0%B6%9C%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%B1-%E0%B6%B8%E0%B6%B8-%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%92%E0%B7%83%E0%B7%92-%E0%B6%AF%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%BA%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%8A-%E0%B6%9A%E0%B6%BB%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%99-%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%91-%E0%B6%B8%E0%B7%92%E0%B7%82%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%BD%E0%B7%8A-%E0%B6%AF%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%BD%E0%B7%8A%E0%B7%84%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%8F|title=I'm not doing anything to maintain my popularity|date=7 May 2019|publisher=Resa|accessdate=7 May 2019}}</ref> The story talks about the journey of a mother, portrayed by [[Umayangana Wickramasinghe]] and daughter going in searching of the missing father by facing many life challenges. The plot depicts the emotional and cognitive characteristics of village folks due to their financial struggle.In an interview for the national newspaper [[Mawbima]], Dilhara said that her starring role in [[Sudu andagena kalu awidin]] marked a significant turning point in her acting career.[[Sudu andagena kalu awidin]] television series won the [[Sumathi Most Popular Teledrama Award]] 2019<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mawbima.lk/sunday-mawbima/10/sundaymawbima-more/1126|title=Michelle has been changed|publisher=[[Mawbima]]|language=Sinhala|date=30 March 2019|accessdate=30 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.lakbima.lk/index.php/gossip/mishel-dilhara|title=Ayoma is a terning point in my life|newspaper=[[Lakbima]] |date=19 April 2019 |accessdate=19 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.pressreader.com/@Michelle_Dilhara/csb_mPjeyPtERmUr3U0xMTWSDPv5qcb3P3v_sYe3SwBZXtSHl_xhfY-qamv46rz2MASi|title=Sudu Andagena Kalu Awidin from Today|newspaper=[[PressReader]] |date=19 March 2019 |accessdate=19 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/interviews/2019/04/25/4777/%E0%B7%83%E0%B7%94%E0%B6%AF%E0%B7%94-%E0%B6%87%E0%B6%B3%E0%B6%9C%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%B1-%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%85%E0%B7%94-%E0%B6%87%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%AF%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%8A-%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%8F%E0%B7%81%E0%B6%BA-%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%99%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%BA%E0%B7%92-%E0%B6%B8%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%BD%E0%B6%BA%E0%B7%92-%E0%B6%B4%E0%B7%8A%E2%80%8D%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%81%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%9A|title=It's not a about Sudu andagena kalu awidin drama , it's about the payment|newspaper=[[Sarasaviya]]|language=Sinhala|date=25 April 2019|accessdate=25 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/interviews/2019/05/02/4931/%E0%B6%AF%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%B6%E0%B7%83%E0%B7%8A-%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%90%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%92-%E0%B6%B4%E0%B7%8A%E2%80%8D%E0%B6%BB%E0%B6%B0%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%B1-%E0%B6%A0%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%AD%E0%B6%BA%E0%B6%9A%E0%B6%A7-%E0%B6%B8%E0%B7%8F%E0%B7%80-%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%9D%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%9C%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%B1|title=Michelle got a main character with no dialogues |newspaper=[[Sarasaviya]]|language=Sinhala|date=2 May 2019|accessdate=2 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.saaravita.lk/latest_news/620346/%e0%b7%83%e0%b7%94%e0%b6%af%e0%b7%94-%e0%b6%87%e0%b6%b3%e0%b6%9c%e0%b7%99%e0%b6%b1-%e0%b6%9a%e0%b7%85%e0%b7%94-%e0%b6%87%e0%b7%80%e0%b7%92%e0%b6%af%e0%b7%92%e0%b6%b1%e0%b7%8a|title=I got a different character in Sudu Andagena Kalu Awidin|date=4 May 2019|publisher=Saaravita|accessdate=4 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dinamina.lk/2019/05/27/%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%92%E0%B7%81%E0%B7%9A%E0%B7%82%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%82%E0%B6%9C/74095/%E2%80%98%E0%B6%85%E0%B6%BA%E0%B7%9D%E0%B6%B8%E0%B7%8F%E2%80%99-%E0%B6%B8%E0%B6%9C%E0%B7%9A-%E0%B6%BB%E0%B6%82%E0%B6%9C%E0%B6%B1-%E0%B6%AF%E0%B7%92%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%BA-%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%83%E0%B7%8A-%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%85%E0%B7%8F|title=The character Ayoma changed my career|publisher=[[Dinamina]]|language=Sinhala|date=27 May 2019|accessdate=27 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://divaina.com/daily/index.php/visheshanga3/29434-2019-06-13-13-57-54|title=Sudu andagena kalu awidin everybody is mad director Sunil costa |newspaper=[[Divaina]] |date=12 June 2019 |accessdate=12 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.silumina.lk/2019/06/22/%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%83%E0%B6%B3%E0%B7%94%E0%B6%B1/%E0%B7%83%E0%B7%94%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%BD%E0%B7%8A-%E0%B7%83%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%8A-%E0%B6%B8%E0%B6%A7-%E0%B6%B8%E0%B7%8F%E0%B7%80-%E0%B6%85%E0%B6%B8%E0%B6%AD%E0%B6%9A-%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%99%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%8A%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%8F|title=Sunil sir made me forget who I am|newspaper=[[Silumina]] |date= 22 June 2019|accessdate=22 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dailymirror.lk/print/news-features/Sudu-andagena-kalu-awidin-99-episodes-of-reality/131-174995|title=Sudu andagena kalu awidin\u2019 99 episodes of reality|newspaper=[[The Daily Mirror (Sri Lanka)|The Daily Mirror]] |date=24 September 2019 |accessdate=24 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/news/2019/10/31/11657/%E0%B7%84%E0%B7%9C%E0%B6%B3-%E0%B6%AF%E0%B7%9A-%E0%B6%A2%E0%B6%B1%E0%B6%B4%E0%B7%8A%E2%80%8D%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%BA%E0%B6%BA%E0%B7%92|title=Best things are popular|newspaper=[[Sarasaviya]]|language=Sinhala|date=31 Oct 2019|accessdate=31 Oct 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Sumathi Award winners 2019 |url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/news-features/2019/10/31/11638/2019-\u0dc3\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dad\u0dd2-\u0dc3\u0db8\u0dca\u0db8\u0dcf\u0db1|publisher=Sarasaviya}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://epaper.resa.lk/2019/12/10/pg08_2.jpg|title=Sudu andagena kalu awidin a teledrama which gives a new path to amateur actors |newspaper=Resa |date=11 Dec 2019 |accessdate=11 Dec 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019 Dilhara was casted for the television series Haratha Hera ( King of Hearts ), aired in [[Independent Television Network]] and directed by Chandika Wijayasena. Dilhara plays the role of a wealthy girl named Pabasara, who is the only daughter of a well known Minister. After completing her higher studies she returns from abroad and re-unites with her friends. But her sole intention is to get everyone to work with her father. The overall story talks about the damage caused due to black money and how people are deliberately fallen into the business of black money.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/teledramas/2019/02/21/3078/%E0%B6%A0%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%AF%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%9A%E0%B6%BD%E0%B7%8F-%E0%B6%AF%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%AF%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%8A-%E0%B7%84%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%BB%E0%B6%AD-%E0%B7%84%E0%B7%9A%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%A7-%E0%B6%85%E0%B6%AD-%E0%B6%AD%E0%B6%B6%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%92|title=Two Chandika's started Haratha Hera|newspaper=[[Sarasaviya]]|language=Sinhala|date=21 February 2019|accessdate=21 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dailynews.lk/2019/03/12/entertainment/179923/matters-heart|title=Matters of the heart |newspaper=[[Daily News (Sri Lanka)|Daily News]] |date=12 March 2019 |accessdate=12 December 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dinamina.lk/2019/02/26/%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%92%E0%B7%81%E0%B7%9A%E0%B7%82%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%82%E0%B6%9C/69483/%E0%B6%85%E0%B6%AF-%E0%B6%A7%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%BD%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%A7%E0%B7%8A%E2%80%8D%E0%B6%BA%E0%B6%9A%E0%B6%BD%E0%B7%8F%E0%B7%80-%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%BA%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%9A-%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%B1%E0%B6%B8-%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%90%E0%B6%B1%E0%B6%9A |title=Today the teledrama industry is going on a wrong direction|publisher=[[Dinamina]]|language=Sinhala|date=26 February 2019|accessdate=26 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.silumina.lk/2019/05/11/%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%83%E0%B6%B3%E0%B7%94%E0%B6%B1/%E0%B6%AD%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%94-%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%9C%E0%B6%BB%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%94%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%94|title=Two Chandika's started Haratha Hera|newspaper=[[Silumina]] |date=14 October 2018 |accessdate=14 October 2018 }}</ref>\n\n'''Hosting Swarnavahini Weekend Vinode'''\nMichelle Dilhara hosted Weekend Vinode Entertainment television program series along with Uditha Abeyrathne and Rukshana Dissanayake aired every Saturday on [[Swarnawahini]]. The program was tended to showcase the singing, dancing and entertainment competitions between a group of audiences that changes every week. Selected people from the audience are allowed to participate in the singing, dancing and other competitions and the winners get a cash prize every week. The program featured singing artists who appeared every week to perform their solos and to entertain the audience.<ref name=\"Mawbima\"/>\n\n==Filmography==\n{{main|Michelle Dilhara filmography}}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n\n<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.silumina.lk/2018/12/29/%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%83%E0%B6%B3%E0%B7%94%E0%B6%B1/%E0%B7%83%E0%B6%B8%E0%B7%8F%E0%B6%A2-%E0%B7%83%E0%B7%9A%E0%B7%80%E0%B6%BA-%E0%B6%9A%E0%B6%BB%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%9A-%E0%B6%BA%E0%B6%A7%E0%B7%92-%E0%B6%85%E0%B6%BB%C2%AD%E0%B6%B8%E0%B7%94%C2%AD%E0%B6%AB%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%8A-%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%B8%E0%B7%99%E0%B6%BA%E0%B7%92 |title=I don't expect anything from social service|newspaper=[[Silumina]] |date=29 December 2018  |accessdate=29 December 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.navaliya.com/2018/12/24/navaindex.htm|title=Young generation can change the world |date=24 December 2018|publisher=[[Navaliya]]|accessdate=24 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/features/2018/12/20/1773/%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%85-%E0%B7%84%E0%B7%9C%E0%B6%B3%E0%B6%A7-%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%85-%E0%B7%84%E0%B7%9C%E0%B6%B3%E0%B6%9A%E0%B7%8A|title=Appreciation for what have done|newspaper=[[Sarasaviya]]|language=Sinhala|date=20 December 2016|accessdate=20 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.saaravita.lk/latest_news/638461/%e0%b6%b8%e0%b7%92%e0%b7%82%e0%b7%99%e0%b6%bd%e0%b7%8a%e0%b6%a7-%e0%b6%ad%e0%b7%80%e0%b6%ad%e0%b7%8a-%e0%b7%83%e0%b6%b8%e0%b7%8a%e0%b6%b8%e0%b7%8f%e0%b6%b1%e0%b6%ba%e0%b6%9a%e0%b7%8a|title=Michelle receives another award|date=2 October 2019|publisher=Saaravita|accessdate=2 October 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Raigam Tele111\">{{cite web|url=http://divaina.com/daily/index.php/welanda/39892-27-38|title=Raigam Tele'es releases the list of award nominees|date=4 March 2020|publisher=[[Divaina]]|accessdate=4 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.sundayobserver.lk/2020/03/08/business/raigam-tele%E2%80%99es-nominees-evening-mobitel|title=Raigam Tele\u2019es Nomi